                <h1>The Yellow Wallpaper: A Feminist Analysis</h1>
                <p>The Yellow Wallpaper is a landmark feminist text that explores themes of mental illness and female repression. Through the narrator's descent into madness within the confines of a patriarchal structure, Charlotte Perkins Gilman critiques societal norms that stifle women's creativity and autonomy, highlighting the dire consequences of such oppression.</p>
